Description:
Central Cranbourne Living! Renovators Dream! Value Add!
Prime location! Situated on a huge block of 622 square meters, central to all shopping centres, easy access to highways, surrounded by a beautiful large park and reserves, offering an abundance of opportunities, this home is a renovators delight!
Enjoy the large living area and dining area as you walk through the front door, stunning floorboards and tiles create the beautiful warmth in this home. Embrace the kitchen, offering perfect foundations for a renovators touch, with ample cupboard space, and large windows, overlooking an incredibly impressive undercover alfresco area with a built-in bar and wood fire. Perfect for entertaining guests all year round.
Offering three bedrooms, all freshly painted with built in wardrobes, a central bathroom with a separate toilet, and a large laundry with external access. In addition, you will find a veranda around the whole house, a large 2 car garage and long driveway.
This home is perfect for those who would like to invest, currently tenanted on a month to month basis. Be quick to snatch this beauty, with astounding potential and the enormous block size, this home is an opportunity you won't want to miss!

Description:
A CUT ABOVE THE REST!
The location of the house is better than best! Set in the Carlisle Park estate, right in the heart of it! Walking distance to all the basic facilities. If you are looking for a house which will meet all your property needs at once, you are at the right place!
This beautifully built, presented and maintained house is just what a family could ask for...4 bedrooms, Plus a study. Master bedroom with full ensuite and WIR. Other bedrooms are very generously spaced and have a lovely central bathroom to cater to them.
No dearth of living space in the house, with 2 large living areas. The front lounge for formal living, complete with carpets. While the second living areas has easy maintainable tiled floor.
The kitchen is a beauty, with full utility. Top quality bench tops and cooking range, dishwasher and plenty of storage space.
The house is fully equipped for comfortable living with evaporative cooling and ducted heating facilities. The beauty of the house is accentuated by Downlights, which would also help cut down the power bills.
The most appealing feature of the property has to be the ample open area at the back! Fit for entertaining, playing with kids, barbecue... the options are endless.
The Features of the House:
- Open Plan Kitchen/ Family & Dining
- Stainless Steel Appliances / Range Hood / Dishwasher
- Ducted Heating & Evaporative Cooling
- Low Maintenance Garden At Front
- Double Lockup Garage
- Downlights
- Side Excess Trailer Or Boat
- Two Separate Living Areas
- Decking at Front
Walking Distance & Short Drive Facilities:
Cranbourne Home Maker Centre, Springhill Shopping Centre, Thompson Park way Shops, Child care facilities, Carlisle Park Primary school, Sporting facilities, Number of Gym's, Medical Centre, Merinda Park Train Station... it's sure to give your car a good rest!
This one is sure to sell in the blink of an eye, So don't waste and minute and give Hardeep Singh a call now to book and inspection. PHOTO ID REQUIRED AT OPEN HOMES.

Description:
The Perfect Starter Or Investment.
Are you looking for a good sized first home or the ideal investment? This is the property for you and it's all located close to quality schools, parks, public transport, Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre and a short drive to Fountain Gate Shopping Centre, the Monash freeway and all other amenities. This amazing property proudly boasting:
- Two separate living zones
- Spacious kitchen with plenty of bench space
- 4 good sized bedrooms
- Ducted Heating and Split System Cooling
- Double carport and Single Garage
- Good sized backyard with multiple Garden Sheds.
- Close to all amenities.
- Plus much more...
All this value makes it a great first home or the ideal inclusion into your property portfolio. For more information on this beautiful property, Call a member of Team May.

A great first home or fantastic investment opportunity, come see for your-self.

Description:
What a gem on a 620m2 block (approx.)
O'Brien Real Estate is proud to present this immaculate little gem nestled in the heart of Cranbourne on a 620m2 block (approx.) that could lend itself to subdivision (STCA). With only a short drive to Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre and local schools and walking distance to the Cranbourne train station, bus stops and the corner store location couldn't get much better! This neat and tidy home features:
- Three Bedrooms, master and second bedrooms both with built in double wardrobes.
- Spacious front lounge and dining room with split system cooling.
- Large kitchen with stainless steel appliances, integrated dishwasher and plenty of cupboard space.
- Outdoor entertaining area with merbau decking and remote control awning.
This little gem has plenty more to offer, gas ducted heating, original hardwood timber flooring, double glazed windows to the back of the house, alarm system, NBN, large garage/work shed, plenty of space to park cars and low maintenance gardens. I wouldn't wait on this one, it will run out the door! Call Victor from O'Brien Real Estate today!

Description:
**GRAND OPEN FOR INSPECTION SATURDAY FEBRUARY 3 AT 11.00AM-11.20AM AND 3.30PM-3.50PM**
CRANBOURNE CENTRAL - Set on a generous block measuring approximately 622 sqm close to all amenities, why not take a peek inside this renovated, recently painted and rendered 3 bedroom, 2 bathroom property, boasting some tremendous features? This welcoming home has been reinvented to reflect an updated and open plan living style. Great lounge area with stunning feature wall and decorative furnace will give a glowing ambiance on those cooler evenings. Pretty as a picture, cosy and comfortable and plenty of room to relax, you'll love the open plan kitchen/meals area with wall mounted air conditioning and big, bright windows. Out the back is a great sized yard, just waiting for a home cricket match and family bbq under the covered alfresco area which can be used year round for relaxing. With a large garden shed, there is plenty of room for that extra bit of storage or create a workshop for the home handy person, or knock it down, subdivide and start your property investment portfolio! The choice is yours. All in all, a top home with top inclusions in an absolutely top location! This home is so close to all that Cranbourne central has to offer including only minutes walk to the local Camms Road shopping strip, medical and dental surgeries. Cranbourne West Primary School is a few minutes away and Cranbourne West (Sandhurst) Shopping Centre boasting a massive Coles Supermarket, medical centre, pharmacy and specialty stores. Cranbourne railway station is a good 15 minute walk or catch the bus at the end of the street and you can also be at Merinda Park railway station or Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre. Casey Fields and Casey Race are a few minutes drive away for those who have a budding sportsperson in their home or like to go swimming at the local pool and enjoy excellent gym facilities.
Other important features including:
** En suite to master bedroom
** Family bathroom with separate shower, vanity and bathtub
** Built-in-Robes to all bedrooms
** Gas ducted heating
** Air conditioning
** Spacious lounge
** Quality tiled entrance
** Beautiful Tasmanian Oak floorboards throughout
** Hostess kitchen with gas cooking
** Large garden shed for storage
** Wall mounted televisions in two bedrooms included with remotes
Cranbourne Central
The central area of Cranbourne is one of the most established and sought after areas. With a mix of older homes on larger blocks and units. Located within walking distance to all facilities, including the newly renovated Cranbourne Park, a range of restaurants, Cranbourne Secondary College and Cranbourne Train Station. Cranbourne Central provides the perfect combination for any resident. PHOTO ID REQUIRED AT OPEN HOMES.

Description:
***AUCTION CANCELLED*** PRIME DEVELOPMENT SITE - 836sqm approx.
***AUCTION CANCELLED***
45 Bakewell Street, CRANBOURNE has unlimited potential set on a large block of approx. 836m2 nestled in a blue chip location, surrounded by all of the town centre's local amenities. Ideally suited to investors, developers (STCA), land bankers and even those looking to occupy with the aim to cash in down the track!
A stunning home in its own right, with zoning being in the Activity Centre Zone means that this property has been earmarked by the City of Casey council for conversion into opportunities such as a medical centre or other professional practices. There's also the option for future redevelopment (STCA).
The true central location is what makes this property very appealing! You are literally a brisk walk to High Street, ALDI and the recently revamped Cranbourne Park Shopping Centre allowing you, or your future clients have easy access to an array of shopping outlets and cafes/restaurants.
The property itself makes an immediate impression from the street and will not disappoint when you walk through the front door. A generous lounge room with gas heater and wall air conditioner, with easy access to the kitchen and dining area. The kitchen equipped with gas cook top, oven, plenty of bench and cupboard space. 3 bedrooms all with BIR, the master finished with a walk in robe, then walk-through access to the family bathroom, with over bath shower and separate toilet.
Outside be greeted buy a great undercover pergola area, perfect for all year-round use, mature landscaping with plenty of grassed area for the kids and pets to enjoy. Not to mention the in-ground heated swimming pool. Large garage sits at the end of a long concrete driveway perfect for extra cars, boats, trailers etc.
If you believe in the age-old theory that good real estate revolves around a central location then you won't be disappointed!
BOOK AN INSPECTION TODAY, IT MAY BE GONE TOMORROW! - *PHOTO ID REQUIRED AT OPEN FOR INSPECTIONS*

Description:
YOUR OWN PIECE OF AUSTRALIAN HISTORY CIRCA 1890
(217275) Original Church of England Vicarage (Victorian cottage) in perfect condition retaining the original charm and character but with all modern family requirements in a fantastic location on a HUGE 868m2 block. (Acitivity Centre Zone )
This home is a testament to its present owners exposing the elegance of this period with original features.
Soaring 12ft ceilings in the hallway, Baltic pine flooring, doors and ceilings, ornate cornices and architraves, lead lights and dado paneling, there are 5 fireplaces, but with ducted heating and evaporative cooling throughout it caters for seasonal comforts.
Three bedrooms most with open fireplaces retain the period feel, there are also two toilets and one bathroom in this grand home.
A well-appointed kitchen featuring a five burner stainless steel cooker, granite cooktop and timber bench tops plus dishwasher gives modern conveniences whilst still retaining the character of the original country style home.
We also have a large family room plus dining area and fireplace with gas coonara, timber French doors lead out to a huge cafe blind enclosed patio entertaining area there is also a little computer utility nook area off the laundry.
Workshop, storage sheds, more storage or playroom bungalow for grandchildren and a triple carport just about complete the picture and the photos speak for themselves. Cottage gardens and an original piece of Australian history could be yours, walk to all facilities in minutes.
Inspections by appointment only by calling Frank Barrett.
WE ARE OPEN SUNDAYS.
Vendor states price is negotiable.

Description:
550m2* Cricket in the Backyard!
Alex Scott and Staff are Proud to present 16 Lansell Drive, Cranbourne North. A comfortable three bedroom, one bathroom home with a single carport, set on a massive 550m2* lot. The house has gas heating and convenient general access ensuite bathroom. The location is second to none being walking distance to Courtenay Gardens Primary School, a five minute drive to Lyndhurst Secondary College, St. Therese Primary School and Cranbourne Carlisle Primary School. The property is in walking distance to local buses and Merinda Park train station, shopping precincts and a number of leisure and sporting facilities, parks, reserves and open green spaces. Currently under a periodic lease with vacant possession easy to arrange, currently leased at $270.00 per week.

Description:
LARGE LAND WITH MASSIVE POTENTIAL (STCA)
Attention Investors and Developers. Proud to present one of the best mid range parcel of land with multiple potential. Located in a bowl of a court this home sitting on a large block of land aprox 739sqm is suitable for 3 great townhouses, two huge dwellings or retain the excisting home and build a townhouse at the back. These are just a few options available subject to council approval, Choice is yours. Solid home boasts of large living area, 3 generous size bedrooms, kitchen with dining, separate bathroom and toilet with dual access. Well manicured backyard is flat and plenty of space to have a veggie garden. Plus having the bonus of a shed and steel garage.
Tenants are lovely who have been living in the house for many many years returning $275 per week. Tenants would love to stay but vacant possession too is an option for the right buyer. Perfect opportunity for you to enter the property market with the option of keep current tenants as a long term investment or go ahead with plans and permits for your pet project. Either way you will not regret with the rapid growth seen in one of the fastest growing suburbs in the south eastern corridor.
No two words about the location. Just to mention,

St Peter's College 0.92km
St Agatha's Primary School 0.95km
Cranbourne Park Primary School 1.12km
Cranbourne Secondary College 1.55km
Cranbourne Train station 1.6km

Public bus transport – walking distance
COLES Express – walking distance

Monash Health Care – 1.5 km
